ETHERNET ENABLING PROCEDURE

1. Add the following block into the /home/hdd500Gb/linux-imx/arch/arm/boot/dts/imx6qdl-unicpu.dtsi

&clks {
    assigned-clocks = <&clks IMX6QDL_CLK_ENET_REF>;
    assigned-clock-rates = <50000000>;
};

&fec {
    pinctrl-names = "default";
    pinctrl-0 = <&pinctrl_enet>;
//	phy-connection-type = "rmii";
	phy-mode = "rmii";
	phy-reset-gpios = <&gpio7 7 0>;
	phy-reset-duration = <2>;
//  clocks = <&clks IMX6QDL_CLK_ENET>, <&clks IMX6QDL_CLK_ENET>, <&rmii_clk>;
	status = "okay";
};

After doing the above changes,  make and copy the "imx6dl-unicpu-fav1024768.dtb" into sdcard

2. Unmask the connman service by using the following commands

$ root
$ systemctl unmask connman.service
$ systemctl start connman.service

3. verify whether you can see the eth0 or not by following command

$ ifconfig
